    <div class="web__item-content">
      </br>
      <p class="web__item-text">
        This app is the end result of Wes Bos' <a href="https://learnnode.com/" target="_blank">Learn Node</a> course. While I do have experience working in Node.js environments, I have mostly been focused on the top of the stack doing layout, styling and interaction work.
        I decided to take this course to learn the basics of full stack development with server side JavaScript, creating APIs, and working with databases.
      </p>
      </br>
      <p class="web__item-text">
        The app is a restaurant application which "users can search, geolocate, review and curate their favorite restaurants from around the world."
        It features user authentication using Passport.js, database storage with MongoDB, Ajax REST API, file uploading and image resizing middleware.
        The app uses Pug for templating, allows users to reset their password via email, has error handling, pagination, and geospatial data with Google Maps.
        It also introduced ES2017 concepts such as async + await, and pleny of ES6 features.
      </p>
      </br>
      <p class="web__item-text">
        I really enjoyed making this because it brought me out of my comfort zone and helped me understand the basic concepts of full stack development. While I don't plan on going full stack, I think this will help me work and communicate with engineering teams in the future.
      </p>
